02:08.723 --> 02:10.524
Catherine:
<i>This is Dr. Catherine Santoro.</i>

02:10.559 --> 02:14.695
<i>Adam Warren, session eight,
code number 6433.</i>

02:18.233 --> 02:19.491
Catherine: <i>Morning, Adam.</i>

02:20.285 --> 02:21.905
<i>Anything you want to talk about today?</i>

02:24.571 --> 02:25.572
No.

02:26.192 --> 02:27.296
I think it would help.

02:28.809 --> 02:30.778
Tell me what you did down there
when you woke up each day.

02:32.490 --> 02:33.868
I ate breakfast.

02:34.428 --> 02:35.559
Okay.

02:36.330 --> 02:37.271
Good.

02:37.463 --> 02:38.871
Then what?

02:39.732 --> 02:41.128
We had school.

02:41.788 --> 02:42.583
"We"?

02:43.469 --> 02:44.812
<i>I mean me.</i>

02:45.106 --> 02:46.439
<i>You said "we."</i>

02:47.077 --> 02:49.271
I had school. I read books.

02:49.744 --> 02:51.744
Adam, you were alone for 10 years.

02:53.514 --> 02:54.479
It's perfectly normal

02:54.515 --> 02:56.109
that you'd create a companion
in your mind.

02:56.850 --> 02:58.437
Is that what you did?

03:00.293 --> 03:01.232
Yeah.

03:01.528 --> 03:03.510
<i>Can you tell me more about your friend?</i>

03:04.318 --> 03:05.463
<i>Does he have a name?</i>

03:06.347 --> 03:07.085
Ben.

03:07.312 --> 03:08.578
Where did Ben come from?

03:09.551 --> 03:10.683
<i>Nowhere.</i>

03:10.718 --> 03:12.316
<i>Does he have a family like you?</i>

03:13.959 --> 03:15.089
<i>He has nothing.</i>

03:15.124 --> 03:16.386
What do you mean?

03:16.553 --> 03:18.052
[Breathes deeply]

03:18.275 --> 03:20.871
They just moved him around all the time.

03:21.253 --> 03:22.635
Like a foster kid?

03:23.949 --> 03:25.655
<i>It makes sense
that you would create someone</i>

03:25.691 --> 03:27.190
<i>who's had
a very different life than you.</i>

03:27.660 --> 03:29.204
Is Ben still with you now?

03:29.560 --> 03:30.659
No.

03:31.280 --> 03:32.717
<i>Do you miss talking to him?</i>

03:32.864 --> 03:33.930
<i>No.</i>

03:33.965 --> 03:36.351
<i>He got you through
a very traumatic experience,</i>

03:36.387 --> 03:38.121
<i>so it makes sense if you...</i>

03:38.963 --> 03:40.630
<i>I never want to see him again.</i>

03:42.573 --> 03:45.506
♪♪

04:39.202 --> 04:45.220
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

04:48.463 --> 04:50.796
[Keyboard clacking]

04:50.832 --> 04:52.865
[Sighs]

04:55.837 --> 04:57.865
Do you ever sleep?

04:58.138 --> 05:00.418
I'll sleep when I'm
in the governor's mansion.

05:02.477 --> 05:03.640
Coffee?

05:03.676 --> 05:04.703
In the pot.

05:07.526 --> 05:08.981
You need the Wi-Fi?

05:09.015 --> 05:11.483
I assume you're Pretty Fly for a Wi-Fi.

05:11.518 --> 05:12.784
Otherwise, your neighbor

05:12.819 --> 05:14.919
is using your phone number
as his password,

05:14.955 --> 05:16.131
and you should move.

05:17.090 --> 05:19.724
You are way too together
to be in my bed.

05:19.759 --> 05:21.559
I'm not always together.

05:21.595 --> 05:22.759
Like when?

05:22.795 --> 05:24.880
[Sighs] Now.

05:26.684 --> 05:28.532
Because I'm a girl?

05:29.719 --> 05:31.768
Because you're a human.

05:33.606 --> 05:36.166
[Cellphone buzzes]

05:36.201 --> 05:37.735
Ugh.

05:38.808 --> 05:40.711
What?

05:42.457 --> 05:43.294
Are you...

05:44.048 --> 05:46.015
That meeting wasn't on my calendar.

05:46.784 --> 05:48.362
I didn't see it.

05:49.153 --> 05:51.787
Uh, no, I-I can't right now.

05:52.674 --> 05:53.857
Of course I'm at home.

05:53.892 --> 05:55.124
Uh, yeah.

05:55.159 --> 05:56.592
Mom, I'll be right there!

05:57.027 --> 05:58.259
Just calm down!

05:59.001 --> 05:59.962
Listen, I'm telling you this

05:59.997 --> 06:01.630
'cause I trust you not to say anything,

06:01.665 --> 06:04.720
but she's been in rough shape
since Dad's affair came out.

06:05.402 --> 06:07.536
Yeah, we're... we're running
out of Kleenex here,

06:07.571 --> 06:10.600
so I'm trying to get her head
in the game for the debate.

06:12.009 --> 06:14.263
You'll just have to handle
this one without me.

06:15.210 --> 06:17.008
Yes, you can.

06:17.383 --> 06:20.228
Yes, you... Ryan, grow a pair.

06:21.050 --> 06:22.660
[Sighs]

06:25.505 --> 06:26.120
What?

06:26.155 --> 06:28.055
That was a really good lie.

06:28.090 --> 06:31.257
[Chuckles] I'm a really good liar.

06:41.369 --> 06:42.866
John: What's all that?

06:44.105 --> 06:45.872
I'm getting rid of it.

06:47.442 --> 06:48.907
Even monkey?

06:48.943 --> 06:50.414
I'm not a little kid anymore.

06:52.245 --> 06:53.679
Copy that.

06:56.784 --> 06:58.062
Oh. Late night?

06:58.518 --> 06:59.851
Willa: Early morning.

06:59.887 --> 07:01.319
Oh? Did you go to church?

07:01.354 --> 07:03.254
- No.
- Oh, maybe you should.

07:03.290 --> 07:05.089
I bet God has a lot to say to you.

07:05.124 --> 07:06.924
What's your problem?

07:08.108 --> 07:10.194
I'm just enjoying the irony.

07:10.229 --> 07:12.548
Why don't you focus on yourself instead?

07:12.861 --> 07:15.713
You've got to step all this
business up a notch tonight.

07:15.748 --> 07:17.367
All of it. No surprises.

07:17.403 --> 07:19.770
A buzzed Danny is still a drunk Danny.

07:19.806 --> 07:21.105
And wear a proper suit.

07:21.140 --> 07:23.584
Not your jean tuxedo.

07:24.076 --> 07:25.274
Touchy.

07:25.310 --> 07:26.436
[Sighs]

07:26.589 --> 07:28.344
Let's talk about Dad's affair.

07:28.379 --> 07:28.725
[Snickers]

07:29.881 --> 07:30.847
Wow.

07:31.583 --> 07:33.049
We can't ignore it.

07:33.085 --> 07:34.239
It's all over the news.

07:34.480 --> 07:36.012
Thanks to you.

07:36.127 --> 07:38.194
The overnight polls
show women voters are loving it,

07:38.389 --> 07:39.354
as I predicted.

07:39.389 --> 07:42.057
Their husbands all cheat,
so they're with you.

07:42.093 --> 07:44.689
But it's still important
we show a united front tonight.

07:44.725 --> 07:47.129
When the debate ends,
you'll be at Mom's side,

07:47.164 --> 07:48.590
contrite but adoring.

07:48.615 --> 07:50.533
Bill and Hillary, John and Jackie.

07:50.569 --> 07:52.364
We're not reinventing the wheel here.

07:52.389 --> 07:55.036
You'll hold hands onstage.
You'll have your moment.

07:55.061 --> 07:57.230
And then the rest of us
will join, Adam in the middle.

07:57.537 --> 07:59.537
This is our chance to remind voters

07:59.572 --> 08:02.156
that Claire Warren represents
strong family values.

08:07.181 --> 08:08.490
Represent.

08:14.668 --> 08:17.001
Well, here's the bad news.

08:17.337 --> 08:19.424
The pipe under the sink's been leaking.

08:19.740 --> 08:22.039
It, uh, rotted out the wood
under the drawer tracks.

08:22.617 --> 08:24.008
Okay.

08:24.043 --> 08:27.812
And then the hinges rusted over
on the kitchen cabinet,

08:27.848 --> 08:29.329
so we'll have to replace those, too.

08:29.867 --> 08:31.313
What's the good news?

08:31.851 --> 08:33.278
I can probably get it done today.

08:33.452 --> 08:34.717
Wow.

08:34.988 --> 08:36.220
That's great.

08:36.455 --> 08:37.724
- I like to work fast.
- [Engine starts]

08:38.506 --> 08:40.273
I'll uh,... I'll write it up.

08:46.747 --> 08:49.281
[Vehicle approaching]

08:51.018 --> 08:53.818
♪♪

09:16.109 --> 09:17.708
[Indistinct conversations]

09:19.036 --> 09:21.723
_

09:29.356 --> 09:30.488
Hi.

09:30.524 --> 09:31.738
You came.

09:33.427 --> 09:35.325
Hi.

09:40.334 --> 09:42.467
Look. I got the mast up.

09:50.250 --> 09:52.148
We can't be friends anymore, Adam.

09:53.576 --> 09:54.688
Why?

09:56.204 --> 09:57.825
I'm a lot older than you.

09:57.897 --> 09:58.958
So?

09:59.464 --> 10:00.858
So you should...

10:01.768 --> 10:03.701
play with kids your own age.

10:03.896 --> 10:06.897
But you said we could build
a model airplane next.

10:07.106 --> 10:08.570
You promised.

10:13.448 --> 10:18.439
Friends should want what's best
for each other, right?

10:20.843 --> 10:22.759
What I want...

10:24.386 --> 10:26.045
isn't the best for you.

10:31.073 --> 10:32.056
Here.

10:32.108 --> 10:33.711
Go get yourself some ice cream.

10:36.026 --> 10:37.568
Go on.

10:43.605 --> 10:46.639
[Whistling]

10:46.664 --> 10:47.464
Hey, what is that?

10:47.503 --> 10:49.158
[Dog barking]

10:51.073 --> 10:53.173
Come on. What's that?

10:53.208 --> 10:55.142
Hey.

11:00.617 --> 11:02.449
Hey, question about the Warren case.

11:02.485 --> 11:03.617
Yeah?

11:03.652 --> 11:06.187
Did he wrap it before he tapped it?

11:06.222 --> 11:07.421
Bite me.

11:07.456 --> 11:10.959
So, that's your type... Mr. Sad Dad?

11:11.427 --> 11:13.741
My type's pretty much anyone but you.

11:13.949 --> 11:15.232
I'm easy like that.

11:15.872 --> 11:17.038
- Parker.
- Parker: Yeah?

11:17.300 --> 11:20.133
I need you to run the addresses
on 100 North 45th Street

11:20.168 --> 11:21.043
between Austin and Pine.

11:21.078 --> 11:22.480
- What are you looking for in that area?
- Foster home.

11:22.505 --> 11:23.727
Sure.
Thank you.

11:23.972 --> 11:25.972
- [Elevator bell dings]
- I'm an idiot.

11:26.068 --> 11:27.235
Could be.

11:27.389 --> 11:29.156
But we got our best
circulation numbers to date

11:29.181 --> 11:30.282
for that affair trash.

11:30.318 --> 11:32.051
I had the biggest story of my career,

11:32.076 --> 11:33.322
- and I dropped it.
- What do you mean?

11:33.496 --> 11:34.962
Willa Warren is a liar.

11:34.987 --> 11:38.226
She is a pathological,
manipulative, lying liar

11:38.251 --> 11:39.317
who lies for a living.

11:39.342 --> 11:40.574
That's funny. So?

11:40.609 --> 11:41.541
So I bought it.

11:41.595 --> 11:43.329
I had a negative paternity test
on the kid,

11:43.471 --> 11:44.470
and I still bought

11:44.495 --> 11:45.399
her lame, half-assed excuse.

11:45.424 --> 11:46.971
And somehow landed a better story.

11:47.422 --> 11:49.455
What's better than Adam Warren
isn't Adam Warren?

11:49.804 --> 11:51.432
That his older sister is in on it.

11:51.720 --> 11:53.653
Gabe: <i>It's Clements. Call you back.</i>

11:53.689 --> 11:54.821
[Beep]

11:54.856 --> 11:56.289
<i>Now</i> you take a day off?

11:56.325 --> 11:58.057
Come on, Clements. Call me back.

11:58.092 --> 12:00.393
[Knock on door]

12:01.726 --> 12:03.582
You remember a kid named Ben?

12:08.069 --> 12:09.736
How long have you been a foster parent?

12:09.771 --> 12:11.817
Man: Oh, about 20 years.

12:12.625 --> 12:13.926
- [Children crying in distance]
- That's dedication.

12:14.135 --> 12:15.316
Well, it's rewarding.

12:15.749 --> 12:17.016
Pays the bills, too.

12:19.339 --> 12:20.966
I'm not sure how I can help you.

12:22.109 --> 12:23.428
Tell me about Ben.

12:24.350 --> 12:28.218
Oh, he was here 8, maybe 10 years ago.

12:28.261 --> 12:29.107
Was he adopted?

12:29.350 --> 12:30.649
I don't know.

12:30.697 --> 12:32.631
Did they move him to another home?

12:33.366 --> 12:34.663
I don't know.

12:35.414 --> 12:36.975
So, what happened to him?

12:37.604 --> 12:39.571
I have so many coming
and going over the years,

12:39.596 --> 12:41.896
I-I-I really couldn't say.

12:42.893 --> 12:43.520
Ah.

12:43.780 --> 12:46.247
The legal limit is four kids per home.

12:46.282 --> 12:48.750
I count eight cups on the table.

12:48.785 --> 12:50.752
There's no smoke detector,
no fire extinguisher.

12:50.787 --> 12:51.820
There's rat traps under your sofa,

12:51.855 --> 12:54.055
and there's an open bottle
of bleach on the counter.

12:54.090 --> 12:55.924
Not the smartest of ideas at any age,

12:55.959 --> 12:57.758
but actually illegal
in a foster situation

12:57.793 --> 12:58.959
with children under the age of 2...

12:58.995 --> 13:01.228
of which I'm guessing from the
screaming and crying upstairs

13:01.263 --> 13:02.530
you've got more than a few of.

13:02.565 --> 13:04.478
Also a pretty serious
department violation.

13:04.849 --> 13:06.979
What are you doing?
Calling Social Services.

13:08.353 --> 13:10.686
He was 8 or 9.

13:11.336 --> 13:13.099
He ran off one day and disappeared.

13:13.979 --> 13:15.522
There's no report on him.

13:18.028 --> 13:19.659
I didn't want to lose my license.

13:21.276 --> 13:23.831
Even if I had reported it,
it wouldn't have mattered.

13:23.867 --> 13:25.547
There's very little follow-up
in the system.

13:25.572 --> 13:26.590
You know that.

13:29.399 --> 13:30.456
Yeah, I do.

13:31.466 --> 13:33.201
So you won't make the call, then?

13:38.800 --> 13:40.345
I did before I came.

13:44.521 --> 13:46.741
I want to take Adam back
to the day he was kidnapped.

13:47.123 --> 13:48.062
Why?

13:49.024 --> 13:50.991
We have a very promising lead,

13:51.026 --> 13:53.032
but the more details he can
fill in for us, the better.

13:53.092 --> 13:53.991
He was 8 years old.

13:54.026 --> 13:56.335
How do you expect him
to remember one day?

13:57.751 --> 13:59.727
Traumatic events usually stay with you.

14:00.591 --> 14:03.567
Which is why we should wait
and have his shrink here.

14:03.602 --> 14:04.600
No, it needs to be now.

14:04.636 --> 14:06.364
We're closing in on this guy,
and he knows it.

14:06.400 --> 14:07.359
Ben: I'm ready.

14:08.359 --> 14:09.799
I can remember.

14:12.944 --> 14:14.159
Nina: Great.

14:14.426 --> 14:17.994
We'll start off nice and easy, okay?

14:19.044 --> 14:20.503
What were you wearing at the rally?

14:21.852 --> 14:23.823
My mom's campaign T-shirt.

14:24.488 --> 14:25.422
What else?

14:26.360 --> 14:29.769
Blue shirt underneath,
long-sleeved; brown pants.

14:33.367 --> 14:35.706
What about underwear or socks?

14:35.793 --> 14:37.225
How does that help your case?

14:37.260 --> 14:38.426
It's the details.

14:38.461 --> 14:39.644
We're trying to unlock his memory.

14:39.679 --> 14:41.670
- With his underwear?
- They had cars on them.

14:42.973 --> 14:44.148
That's right.

14:48.084 --> 14:48.928
Okay.

14:49.175 --> 14:51.008
Um, I'm gonna show you a...

14:51.043 --> 14:54.669
few images we have on file
from that day.

14:55.535 --> 14:58.881
Just, um... if you bring
anything else up, okay?

15:03.154 --> 15:04.956
Soldani's Pizza.

15:05.249 --> 15:06.402
We had it for dinner.

15:07.769 --> 15:10.317
We always got
the pepperoni and pineapple.

15:10.353 --> 15:11.452
[Chuckles]

15:21.864 --> 15:23.464
That's Alex.

15:23.499 --> 15:25.733
She was in his 3rd-grade class.

15:25.768 --> 15:26.999
I used to babysit her.

15:27.034 --> 15:28.768
Let's give Adam a chance to answer.

15:33.466 --> 15:35.753
She was there. I-I remember her.

15:39.681 --> 15:40.889
What about this one?

15:42.297 --> 15:43.569
Do you recognize him?

15:53.740 --> 15:54.807
Adam?

15:56.997 --> 15:57.948
I think that's enough.

15:58.256 --> 15:59.200
Let Adam answer the question.

15:59.235 --> 16:00.975
He clearly doesn't know him.

16:04.261 --> 16:05.393
<i>-Do</i> you?
- Claire: Stop it!

16:05.429 --> 16:06.962
- Who is he?
- I said it's enough.

16:06.997 --> 16:09.230
- 'Cause he kind of looks a lot...
- Stop it.

16:10.500 --> 16:12.734
What the hell is going on here?

16:20.242 --> 16:22.242
Thank you for your time, Adam.

16:26.920 --> 16:28.754
[Door closes, footsteps approaching]

16:31.252 --> 16:32.451
She might not know.

16:32.486 --> 16:33.718
She knows.

16:33.754 --> 16:34.983
Even if she does, she can't prove it.

16:35.019 --> 16:36.448
She can't even say it out loud.

16:36.473 --> 16:38.349
Not with a positive DNA test,
which we have.

16:38.716 --> 16:40.182
God, what are we doing?

16:40.216 --> 16:42.283
- We are putting our family back together.
- No, no.

16:42.308 --> 16:45.353
We are lying to the police, your father,

16:45.388 --> 16:46.254
and the entire world.

16:47.727 --> 16:50.494
- I will handle this, all right?
- Oh, God.

16:50.530 --> 16:52.530
Have you seen the way that
your dad looks at him?

16:52.565 --> 16:54.081
He's the sun, the moon, the stars.

16:54.106 --> 16:55.877
Just concentrate on the debate tonight,

16:55.912 --> 16:57.721
- and everything will be okay.
- No, it is not okay.

16:57.746 --> 16:59.728
It is fraud on a level so massive...

16:59.763 --> 17:00.752
Mom.

17:00.777 --> 17:03.569
And... and I'm not even sure
if he's worth it.

17:04.192 --> 17:05.491
How can you say that?

17:05.527 --> 17:06.542
How can I not?

17:06.578 --> 17:07.961
I don't know anything about him.

17:07.996 --> 17:09.963
I don't know where he comes from.
I don't know his last name.

17:09.998 --> 17:12.296
I don't even know if he likes
what I make him for breakfast.

17:12.320 --> 17:16.079
This person that you have
brought into our house is...

17:16.271 --> 17:18.464
He is living in Adam's room,
he is sleeping in Adam's bed,

17:18.489 --> 17:20.684
he is throwing away
all of Adam's things,

17:20.709 --> 17:22.023
and I don't even know who he is.

17:22.049 --> 17:24.166
- Mom.
- Tell me who he is.

17:25.012 --> 17:26.974
He's Adam's friend.

17:30.970 --> 17:32.083
That's not good enough.

17:43.991 --> 17:46.025
[Rock music plays]

17:53.479 --> 17:55.246
[Chuckles] Really?

17:55.830 --> 17:57.308
Can't a girl buy a guy a drink?

17:57.343 --> 17:58.422
Mm.

17:59.000 --> 18:02.527
The girl who trashed
my entire family to the world?

18:04.605 --> 18:05.718
Why not?

18:07.968 --> 18:09.178
[Sighs]

18:09.969 --> 18:11.890
Wow. You clean up good.

18:12.391 --> 18:14.358
I'm supposed to be at the debate.

18:14.386 --> 18:16.086
Oh, right. Yeah, that's a big deal.

18:16.111 --> 18:18.236
Yeah. To some people.

18:19.044 --> 18:21.017
Hey, can you tell your mom
when she's governor

18:21.052 --> 18:23.225
that I have a really big
pothole on my street?

18:23.259 --> 18:26.113
I am sure that she will
make that a priority.

18:28.452 --> 18:30.514
So, why are you bailing on this thing?

18:33.391 --> 18:34.802
I don't know.

18:37.642 --> 18:40.777
Behind every great politician
stands a great family, right?

18:40.812 --> 18:41.762
Right.

18:42.380 --> 18:43.511
When I'm not there.

18:44.090 --> 18:46.362
Our nation was created by rejects.

18:53.657 --> 18:55.965
So, how's your boyfriend?

18:57.522 --> 18:59.362
People disappoint.

19:01.178 --> 19:02.290
Yeah.

19:07.930 --> 19:08.832
Ben: Hello?

19:12.482 --> 19:13.665
You look nice.

19:15.083 --> 19:16.062
Thanks.

19:18.986 --> 19:21.998
But I think it might be better
if you stayed at home tonight.

19:23.718 --> 19:24.782
[Sighs]

19:25.046 --> 19:26.095
Why?

19:26.894 --> 19:28.563
She's having a hard time with it.

19:29.110 --> 19:31.478
She... she just needs
to get used to you.

19:32.427 --> 19:34.447
What if she doesn't ever get used to me?

19:40.848 --> 19:43.490
I'll leave you some money
for pizza, okay?

19:48.621 --> 19:49.489
Hey.

19:50.283 --> 19:51.511
Didn't you live here with your mom

19:51.536 --> 19:53.417
when I was working here 10 years ago?

19:53.452 --> 19:54.176
Yes.

19:54.211 --> 19:56.074
Oh. How is she?

19:57.663 --> 19:58.874
Not well.

19:59.458 --> 20:00.523
She's dead.

20:03.055 --> 20:04.401
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

20:05.330 --> 20:07.211
She seemed like a nice lady.

20:08.360 --> 20:09.261
She was.

20:09.387 --> 20:11.396
Well, I hope you got
to spend some quality time

20:11.421 --> 20:13.302
with her before she passed.

20:15.033 --> 20:16.531
I was away.

20:18.344 --> 20:20.256
How much is all this gonna cost?

20:23.428 --> 20:24.666
I'll do it for free.

20:26.416 --> 20:27.319
What?

20:28.153 --> 20:29.092
Well...

20:29.780 --> 20:31.580
10 years of faulty cabinets...

20:31.605 --> 20:32.896
Yeah, but that's not your fault.

20:34.225 --> 20:35.356
I feel like I owe you.

20:39.523 --> 20:41.117
Okay. Thanks.

20:42.365 --> 20:43.747
I'll be right back.

20:44.727 --> 20:46.895
[Door opens]

20:59.916 --> 21:03.184
♪♪

21:13.650 --> 21:15.616
[Indistinct conversations]

21:15.760 --> 21:17.393
Mood ring for your girlfriend?

21:17.428 --> 21:18.289
No, thanks.

21:23.434 --> 21:25.566
The guy's in the bathroom or something.

21:30.774 --> 21:32.462
Will he be back soon?

21:32.736 --> 21:34.824
Well, he's been gone for a while.

21:37.594 --> 21:39.400
He sells those birdhouses for $10.

21:39.425 --> 21:40.741
I can take it if you want.

21:46.022 --> 21:47.145
Have a good day.

21:49.599 --> 21:50.353
Hi, there.

21:53.589 --> 21:54.476
Just sold another.

21:54.501 --> 21:55.934
Oh, yeah.

22:05.102 --> 22:06.334
Woman: I should get a cut.

22:06.370 --> 22:08.169
I'm your lucky charm.

22:08.205 --> 22:10.305
[Chuckles]

22:10.340 --> 22:12.207
You really are.

22:16.113 --> 22:17.912
Quality Woodworks!

22:17.947 --> 22:19.146
Come on over.

22:19.181 --> 22:21.982
♪♪

22:27.687 --> 22:29.988
Announcer: Welcome to
the first gubernatorial debate

22:30.023 --> 22:31.024
of the 2016 election.

22:31.059 --> 22:33.511
Coming live to you from the
Augusta Performing Arts Center.

22:33.546 --> 22:38.049
Four years ago, the state of
Maine was in a state of crisis.

22:38.703 --> 22:41.454
But I rolled up my sleeves
and got to work.

22:42.027 --> 22:43.940
<i>During my tenure, I balanced the budget,</i>

22:44.554 --> 22:46.554
<i>pulled us out of a terrible recession,</i>

22:46.590 --> 22:48.936
<i>reduced class size in schools.</i>

22:49.841 --> 22:51.312
<i>We have come a long way.</i>

22:52.262 --> 22:53.643
<i>But we still have a long way to go.</i>

22:54.256 --> 22:55.813
Mayor Warren, your opening statement?

22:55.850 --> 22:56.958
You'll have one minute.

22:57.495 --> 22:59.760
Well, I'm gonna go out on a limb here

22:59.795 --> 23:04.064
and say I completely agree
with Governor Lang

23:04.099 --> 23:05.866
on that last part.

23:05.901 --> 23:07.000
Um...

23:07.036 --> 23:09.296
Is the debate over?
Can I take off these heels yet?

23:09.331 --> 23:10.773
[Laughter] Uh, he's right.

23:11.412 --> 23:12.744
We do have to do better,

23:12.769 --> 23:14.736
but we can't do it under his leadership.

23:14.761 --> 23:17.761
Four years is a long road, Governor.

23:17.852 --> 23:18.651
I get it.

23:19.180 --> 23:21.500
But you've fallen asleep at the wheel,

23:21.636 --> 23:24.417
and good American families
are struggling.

23:24.442 --> 23:25.256
They are hurting.

23:25.376 --> 23:28.534
And when they hurt, we all do.

23:28.569 --> 23:33.114
- [Applause]
- Strong family values are the foundation

23:33.150 --> 23:35.154
of everything
we're talking about tonight.

23:35.179 --> 23:37.254
<i>I know I would not be standing here</i>

23:37.279 --> 23:40.243
<i>if it weren't for the values
my parents instilled in me,</i>

23:40.268 --> 23:43.183
<i>and I can only hope
that I have done the same</i>

23:43.208 --> 23:44.610
<i>for my own children.</i>

23:44.635 --> 23:47.095
[Breathing heavily]

23:57.461 --> 24:01.629
I know that I am not
the only mother out there

24:01.665 --> 24:05.599
who is sick and tired
of our elected leaders

24:05.634 --> 24:09.269
making it harder for me
to protect my family.

24:09.304 --> 24:11.238
10 seconds, Mayor Warren.

24:11.273 --> 24:16.677
<i>Making it harder for us
to keep our children safe,</i>

24:16.712 --> 24:19.366
<i>to provide them with, uh...</i>

24:19.402 --> 24:20.981
Doug: All right, Mr. Asher.

24:21.016 --> 24:23.591
Just sign here, and you're all set.

24:23.627 --> 24:25.652
- Charlie: <i> Here we go.</i>
- Ah.

24:25.687 --> 24:27.514
That's your neighbor, right? The mayor?

24:27.834 --> 24:29.379
- Hank: Yeah.
<i>-Let's go.</i>

24:29.414 --> 24:30.614
Who you voting for?

24:31.546 --> 24:32.493
The other guy.

24:32.518 --> 24:35.339
<i>And let's talk about
how crime in her own city</i>

24:35.375 --> 24:36.979
<i>-has actually increased 18%...</i>
- Thank you.

24:37.004 --> 24:39.026
- Thank you.
<i>- ...under her leadership.</i>

24:39.051 --> 24:43.145
Claire: <i>Yes, because I tripled
the budget of our police force.</i>

24:43.170 --> 24:45.035
<i>So they're arresting more offenders,</i>

24:45.060 --> 24:47.221
<i>and the result is, my city is a safer
place to live.</i>

24:47.246 --> 24:49.765
[Doorbell rings]

24:49.977 --> 24:51.622
Pepperoni pineapple.

24:55.011 --> 24:55.936
Thanks.

25:09.090 --> 25:12.890
Bottom line...
You're a one issue candidate.

25:12.926 --> 25:14.993
Your son was kidnapped.

25:15.028 --> 25:17.061
A terrible thing happened to you.

25:17.097 --> 25:20.598
But since when does that
qualify you to govern a state?

25:20.634 --> 25:24.341
People who have experienced
tragedy deserve our sympathy.

25:24.394 --> 25:26.413
They deserve our understanding.

25:26.449 --> 25:29.832
But they do not automatically
deserve our votes.

25:30.575 --> 25:32.763
You have my understanding.

25:32.798 --> 25:34.845
You have my sympathy.

25:35.492 --> 25:40.430
But what you do not have
is the experience to do my job.

25:40.466 --> 25:42.057
[Applause]

25:42.082 --> 25:44.463
In all due respect,
I think it's a real disservice

25:44.498 --> 25:47.593
to all those other people out
there who've experienced loss

25:47.618 --> 25:49.012
to use your son as a political prop
in this campaign.

25:49.037 --> 25:49.883
Oh, no, no.

25:49.918 --> 25:51.258
Y-Y-You can just stop right there.

25:51.370 --> 25:54.304
You have not met a tragedy
you couldn't use, Claire.

25:54.340 --> 25:56.070
Your son was taken, you ran for mayor.

25:56.106 --> 25:58.499
You got him back, and now you
want us to make you governor.

25:58.780 --> 26:04.492
To be clear, Governor,
I did not get my son back.

26:04.528 --> 26:06.428
[Audience murmuring]

26:18.237 --> 26:19.837
He says he is.

26:20.309 --> 26:22.710
The world believes he is.
A blood test proved he is.

26:22.746 --> 26:24.877
But he's not my son.

26:28.741 --> 26:30.959
My son was taken at 8 years old.

26:31.154 --> 26:32.462
He was a little boy

26:32.492 --> 26:36.707
who loved the ocean,
baseball, his family.

26:37.440 --> 26:38.640
That boy is gone.

26:38.675 --> 26:40.408
He is never coming back.

26:40.443 --> 26:43.711
There is a stranger in his place
that I don't know at all,

26:43.746 --> 26:46.881
and somehow, I have
to learn to accept that.

26:46.916 --> 26:48.149
I hope I can.

26:48.871 --> 26:51.218
<i>And... and you are right, Governor...</i>

26:51.687 --> 26:53.991
<i>My political career has been
shaped by my experiences,</i>

26:54.016 --> 26:55.851
while yours has been shaped
by a fancy last name

26:55.876 --> 26:57.749
on some statues in the State House.

26:57.774 --> 27:00.894
We stand here, and we pretend
that we are debating...

27:00.929 --> 27:03.363
♪♪

27:33.259 --> 27:35.593
[Door creaking]

27:35.629 --> 27:38.362
<i>...vote for me because I was a...</i>

27:41.024 --> 27:42.324
<i>I want people to vote for me</i>

27:42.358 --> 27:44.591
<i>because I am a woman in power</i>

27:44.626 --> 27:46.626
<i>who has seen discrimination firsthand.</i>

27:46.662 --> 27:48.295
<i>And, yes, I want people to vote for me</i>

27:48.331 --> 27:49.463
<i>because my son was taken from us.</i>

27:49.498 --> 27:52.268
<i>That means everything in my power</i>

27:52.304 --> 27:55.132
<i>to enact laws to keep us safe.</i>

27:55.157 --> 27:57.304
<i>It makes sense that you
wouldn't want to acknowledge</i>

27:57.340 --> 27:59.410
<i>that our experiences make us
who we are, Governor,</i>

27:59.446 --> 28:01.407
<i>because you've spent the last four years</i>

28:01.442 --> 28:04.010
<i>in a expensive suit
sitting in a mansion,</i>

28:04.045 --> 28:06.986
<i>looking down on people
with actual problems,</i>

28:07.021 --> 28:09.648
<i>which your policies have handed us.</i>

28:09.684 --> 28:11.517
<i>But we know who you are,</i>

28:11.552 --> 28:14.587
<i>and I think we're ready for a change.</i>

28:14.622 --> 28:17.189
<i>Next question.</i>

28:17.224 --> 28:19.992
♪♪

28:28.976 --> 28:30.109
Hey, Ben.

28:30.404 --> 28:33.670
[Breathing heavily]

28:33.706 --> 28:35.439
Time to have a talk.

28:37.493 --> 28:39.076
Willa: The room was dead silent,

28:39.124 --> 28:42.090
and then the people who are
supposed to tell the media

28:42.144 --> 28:43.977
had nothing to say.

28:44.012 --> 28:45.812
That should tell you... you creamed him.

28:45.846 --> 28:47.577
You... you wiped the floor with him. Oh.

28:47.612 --> 28:49.447
You made him cry for his mommy.

28:49.482 --> 28:51.434
You actually had me
feeling sorry for him.

28:51.470 --> 28:52.915
Would you please make her stop?

28:52.940 --> 28:57.222
It's like the 49ers versus
the Broncos in Super Bowl XXIV.

28:57.257 --> 28:59.582
[Laughs] I don't even know
what that means.

28:59.608 --> 29:02.183
- It means you won.
- No, I stumbled on education.

29:02.208 --> 29:03.129
It is over.

29:03.154 --> 29:04.836
I know I could have hit
him so much harder

29:04.861 --> 29:05.541
on job growth.

29:05.576 --> 29:07.265
- I-I...
- You were great.

29:07.829 --> 29:09.629
You should have come with us, bud.

29:09.665 --> 29:10.430
We missed you.

29:10.465 --> 29:12.519
It's okay. I saw it all from here.

29:16.064 --> 29:18.962
I thought it made a lot
of sense, what you said.

29:26.097 --> 29:27.457
Are you okay?

29:30.649 --> 29:31.762
Yeah. Just tired.

29:31.855 --> 29:32.790
You sure?

29:33.518 --> 29:35.052
There's pizza in the fridge.

29:35.599 --> 29:36.891
Pepperoni and pineapple.

29:44.509 --> 29:46.443
Catherine: <i>This is Dr. Catherine Santoro.</i>

29:46.478 --> 29:50.079
<i>Adam Warren, Session 10,
code number 64386.</i>

29:51.649 --> 29:52.666
[Knock on door]

29:52.813 --> 29:54.113
<i>How are you feeling today, Adam?</i>

29:54.148 --> 29:55.580
[Keyboard clacks]

30:01.655 --> 30:03.794
[Chuckles] The work wife.

30:03.830 --> 30:05.945
He said you were uptight,
but he didn't mention pretty.

30:05.970 --> 30:07.157
Do I know you?

30:08.161 --> 30:10.852
Uh, Jonah Clements, Gabe's husband.

30:10.887 --> 30:12.466
- Hi.
- [Chuckling] Hi.

30:13.020 --> 30:14.352
Is he here?

30:14.387 --> 30:15.620
No. Mnh-mnh.

30:15.656 --> 30:16.759
Is he out working a case?

30:17.296 --> 30:18.927
Oh, he didn't come home last night?

30:19.793 --> 30:21.818
I assumed he was with you.

30:23.433 --> 30:25.989
Agent Clements was last
heard from 36 hours ago.

30:26.049 --> 30:27.582
He's had no communication
with the Bureau,

30:27.618 --> 30:28.916
his husband, or family.

30:28.952 --> 30:30.718
There's been no bank
or credit-card activity

30:30.754 --> 30:31.753
since yesterday afternoon.

30:31.788 --> 30:34.200
I want a BOLO put out
on his car immediately.

30:34.235 --> 30:35.624
Triangulate his cellphone.

30:35.659 --> 30:37.292
Once we get his last-known location,

30:37.327 --> 30:39.761
let's question anyone and
everyone he was in contact with.

30:39.796 --> 30:42.429
This takes top priority, people,
and I want hourly updates.

30:42.465 --> 30:44.133
Let's move! Now!

30:45.693 --> 30:46.716
Nina.

30:48.404 --> 30:49.984
He's probably somewhere sleeping it off.

30:50.078 --> 30:51.244
No, he doesn't do that.

30:51.279 --> 30:53.547
- How do you know?
- Because I know him.

31:10.264 --> 31:11.664
What's your name?

31:19.319 --> 31:20.408
Ben.

31:23.863 --> 31:25.216
Your full name.

31:28.109 --> 31:29.583
Ben Murphy.

31:33.488 --> 31:34.620
Irish?

31:35.635 --> 31:36.956
My grandpa...

31:36.992 --> 31:37.755
I think.

31:42.063 --> 31:43.387
Where were you born?

31:46.594 --> 31:47.580
Minnesota.

31:48.502 --> 31:49.496
I've never been.

31:49.878 --> 31:50.910
It's cold.

31:53.673 --> 31:54.607
Big city?

31:55.991 --> 31:57.274
Little.

32:01.580 --> 32:03.023
Do you like tacos?

32:03.676 --> 32:05.409
I've been making them
at least once a week

32:05.434 --> 32:06.844
because they were Adam's favorite,

32:06.878 --> 32:09.144
but... I don't know... do you like them?

32:09.221 --> 32:10.120
Tacos?

32:12.303 --> 32:13.096
Yeah.

32:14.256 --> 32:15.183
Good.

32:19.117 --> 32:20.113
No. [Chuckles]

32:20.867 --> 32:24.202
They're too spicy the way you make them.

32:25.590 --> 32:26.793
Oh.

32:31.525 --> 32:32.844
Claire...

32:35.148 --> 32:37.222
...I'm sorry I'm not him.

32:38.788 --> 32:40.877
You don't have to call me Claire.

32:43.089 --> 32:44.637
You don't have to spy on me.

33:10.847 --> 33:12.747
[Sighs]

33:45.779 --> 33:48.313
♪♪

33:55.044 --> 33:56.776
Didn't you live here with your mom

33:56.811 --> 33:58.245
when I was working here 10 years ago?

34:00.916 --> 34:02.449
I'll do it for free.

34:03.886 --> 34:05.078
I feel like I owe you.

34:08.456 --> 34:10.382
Well, he's been gone for a while.

34:11.259 --> 34:13.726
♪♪

34:57.674 --> 34:59.207
Willa: Rough night?

35:00.157 --> 35:01.325
What... what?

35:02.233 --> 35:03.492
Where were you?

35:04.181 --> 35:05.185
Out.

35:05.596 --> 35:06.558
With who?

35:09.316 --> 35:10.117
Friend.

35:10.403 --> 35:12.368
Well, Mom killed it.

35:12.635 --> 35:14.852
Pretty much every outlet
is saying she won.

35:15.230 --> 35:16.017
Nice.

35:17.834 --> 35:19.193
Um...

35:21.743 --> 35:23.810
I-I-I messed up.

35:26.076 --> 35:27.018
I'm sorry.

35:27.730 --> 35:28.658
For what?

35:36.097 --> 35:37.313
For...

35:37.994 --> 35:39.775
the debate.

35:41.362 --> 35:42.675
You're absolved.

36:01.372 --> 36:03.807
♪♪

36:03.842 --> 36:06.676
[Indistinct conversations]

36:27.898 --> 36:29.297
Help you with something?

36:30.868 --> 36:32.966
I'd like to speak with Detective Meyer.

36:33.001 --> 36:34.156
She's out.

36:34.181 --> 36:35.557
Want to leave a message?

36:37.407 --> 36:38.406
I'll wait.

36:38.548 --> 36:39.922
Could be a long one.

36:41.271 --> 36:42.526
It's worth it.

36:58.073 --> 37:00.609
- Woman: <i>You have three new messages.</i>
- [Beep]

37:00.634 --> 37:02.405
Gabe: <i> Think I get the bar thing now, kid.</i>

37:02.506 --> 37:04.272
<i>No time to eat on this job.</i>

37:05.106 --> 37:06.301
<i>Fill you in later.</i>

37:08.335 --> 37:09.329
[Beep]

37:13.540 --> 37:15.006
Maybe there's something that would help.

37:15.042 --> 37:16.908
Okay. We'll scan his files.

37:16.943 --> 37:18.910
Can you take this, please?

37:18.945 --> 37:21.546
So, he... he didn't mention
where he was going?

37:23.083 --> 37:25.824
I should have come to you
sooner, but I know the job.

37:25.860 --> 37:27.812
I know the hours that you guys work.

37:28.392 --> 37:29.412
Didn't even occur to me that...

37:29.447 --> 37:30.622
Just hang in there, all right?

37:31.036 --> 37:32.280
We're gonna bring him home.

37:33.573 --> 37:34.660
Okay?

37:39.264 --> 37:41.347
[Cellphone beeps]

37:41.380 --> 37:43.677
<i>Think I get the bar thing now, kid.</i>

37:43.702 --> 37:46.143
<i>No time to eat on this job.</i>

37:46.168 --> 37:49.038
<i>Fill you in later.</i>

37:52.676 --> 37:54.052
[Door creaking]

37:58.415 --> 37:59.829
I'm so sorry.

38:02.272 --> 38:03.635
I'm so sorry.

38:05.276 --> 38:06.718
I'm so sorry.

38:20.297 --> 38:22.431
[Sighs]

38:22.699 --> 38:23.998
Sorry.

38:24.460 --> 38:25.996
I'm so sorry.

38:26.317 --> 38:27.676
Oh, yeah.

38:34.456 --> 38:35.526
I'm sorry.

38:49.818 --> 38:52.031
I am so sorry.

38:58.254 --> 38:59.721
Willa: Cinched the governorship,

38:59.756 --> 39:02.340
and your first move
is to pull out Betty Crocker?

39:02.365 --> 39:03.408
[Chuckles]

39:03.433 --> 39:05.476
It's his birthday next week.

39:06.373 --> 39:07.630
Not Adam's.

39:07.762 --> 39:08.616
<i>His.</i>

39:11.006 --> 39:13.977
Just want to make him something special.

39:17.373 --> 39:18.909
You're a good person, Mom.

39:19.953 --> 39:21.476
[Chuckles] No, I'm not.

39:22.044 --> 39:23.643
You are.

39:27.349 --> 39:28.342
Well...

39:29.051 --> 39:30.339
I'll spend the rest of my life

39:30.375 --> 39:32.515
wishing that he was the one
that got sick down there.

39:33.864 --> 39:34.408
So...

39:35.104 --> 39:36.990
the least I can do is bake him a cake.

39:43.932 --> 39:46.533
♪♪

39:46.568 --> 39:48.119
How did he die?

39:48.704 --> 39:49.523
What?

39:49.548 --> 39:51.243
You said he was trying
to escape or something,

39:51.268 --> 39:54.085
- and then he fell and hit his head.
- So?

39:54.121 --> 39:56.545
So you told her he got sick.

39:56.580 --> 39:57.988
Why are you so upset?

39:58.013 --> 39:59.601
Which is it?

39:59.626 --> 40:02.216
Did he hit his head, or did he get sick?

40:04.572 --> 40:05.771
Both.

40:06.888 --> 40:07.770
What?

40:09.256 --> 40:11.343
He fell and hit his head.

40:13.193 --> 40:14.558
Then he got sick.

40:15.383 --> 40:18.650
He was sweating, and he was burning up,

40:18.759 --> 40:21.917
and I couldn't do anything.

40:24.058 --> 40:25.090
Okay?

40:26.012 --> 40:27.043
Okay.

40:34.754 --> 40:36.520
It's cold out here.

40:43.163 --> 40:44.662
Catherine: <i> What's wrong?</i>

40:46.364 --> 40:47.259
<i>Adam?</i>

40:48.534 --> 40:50.434
<i>Why can't they swim together?</i>

40:50.582 --> 40:51.765
<i>My fish?</i>

40:53.698 --> 40:56.282
Why do they have
to be separated like that?

40:57.603 --> 40:58.811
They're both boys.

40:59.137 --> 41:00.937
They can't be confined together.

41:01.513 --> 41:02.330
Why?

41:03.215 --> 41:04.723
One of them would kill the other.

41:11.628 --> 41:12.611
Adam?

41:16.948 --> 41:18.100
Should we begin?

41:19.589 --> 41:20.658
Yes.

